  "title": "Senior Research and Development Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Lead <strong>electrochemical cell design</strong> and scaling of <strong>acid‑neutralisation</strong> and <strong>air‑contactor </strong>systems from lab to pilot to commercial. Validate commercial designs with pilot data, coordinate with commercial partners, and drive <strong>IP development</strong>.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities </strong></p><ul><li>Design & optimise <strong>electrochemical cells</strong> for scalability and efficiency.</li><li>Scale <strong>acid‑neutralisation systems</strong> from lab data; define pilot design/operating windows.</li><li>Validate commercial designs (carbonation/acid neutralisation, heavy‑metal remediation) using pilot\nresults.</li><li>Translate <strong>air‑contactor </strong>concepts into manufacturable product designs; resolve scale‑up challenges.</li><li>Act as technical liaison with partners (design, construction, commissioning alignment).</li><li>Direct IP strategy with counsel; draft invention disclosures and support patent filings.</li><li>Manage multi‑workstream project plans, deliverables, risks, and reporting.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s/Master’s/PhD in Electrochemistry, Chemical Engineering, or related.</li><li>6–10+ years in electrochemical R&D with <strong>pilot validation</strong> and productidation exposure.</li><li>Strong system‑level thinking and partner management.</li></ul>",
